-- "Realistic" Italy banks will ask for 37 bln euros in ECB TLTROs - minister
-- 
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 01:43PM EDT
-- None



ROME, Sept 16 (Reuters) - Italy's Economy Minister Pier Carlo Padoan said on Tuesday it is "realistic" to estimate that the country's banks will ask for a total of 37 billion euros in the two offers of the European Central Bank's new long-term loan programme (TLTRO) this year.

